panel_name: Ion AmpliSeq<sup>TM</sup> Inherited Cancer Research Panel
panel_desc: The Ion AmpliSeq<sup>TM</sup> Inherited Cancer Research Panel provides a quick, accurate and cost effective way to identify genetic mutations in 134 genes associated with inherited cancers. This panel is designed based on extensive curation of peer-reviewed literature, disease research databases and consultation with key opinion leaders. This panel helps in research to identify specific genetic causes of inherited cancers which can be difficult because of pleiotropy, locus heterogeneity and accessibility of information.This panel is to be used for research use only and not for use in diagnostic procedures.This panel is to be used for research use only and not for use in diagnostic procedures.

panel_name: Ion AmpliSeq<sup>TM</sup> BRCA Plus, Extended Hereditary Breast and Ovarian Research Panel
panel_desc: Approximately 7-10% of breast and ovarian cancers are hereditary. BRCA1 & BRCA2 tumor suppressor genes account for a high number of these cases, but few other hereditary cancer related genes are associated with the risk to develop breast and/or ovarian cancer. The panel was developed as a research method to identify genetic mutations associated with inherited breast and ovarian cancers. The panel assesses 11 genes known to harbour mutations related to breast and/or ovarian cancer (ATM, BRCA1, BRCA2, CHEK2, PALB2, RAD51C, RAD51D, NBN, CDH1, SMARCA4, TP53). The panel was validated in 3 laboratories using 45 samples.This panel is to be used for research use only and not for use in diagnostic procedures.

panel_name: Ion AmpliSeq<sup>TM</sup> Comprehensive Ovarian Cancer Research Panel
panel_desc: The Ion AmpliSeq<sup>TM</sup> Comprehensive Ovarian Cancer Research Panel provides a quick, accurate and cost effective way to identify genetic germline mutations in 41 genes associated with inherited ovarian cancer. This panel is designed based on extensive curation of peer-reviewed literature, disease research databases and consultation with key opinion leaders. This panel helps in the research to identify specific genetic causes of inherited ovarian cancer which can be difficult because of pleiotropy, locus heterogeneity and accessibility of information.This panel is to be used for research use only and not for use in diagnostic procedures.

panel_name: Ion AmpliSeq<sup>TM</sup> Colon and Lung Cancer Panel

The Ion AmpliSeq<sup>TM</sup> Comprehensive Cancer Panel is the most extensive cancer panel compiled by reviewing research literature and databases. This is a result of a broad survey of hundreds of key tumor suppressor genes and oncogenes implicated in cancer research encompassing over 50% of the COSMIC Cancer Gene Census from Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute. This panel of 409 genes is strategically designed to interrogate multiple gene families simultaneously, pathway-based gene selection profiles, cancer driver genes along with signaling cascades, apoptosis, DNA repair, transcription regulators, inflammatory response, and growth factor genes in a single assay.This panel is to be used for research use only and not for use in diagnostic procedures.
